# Architecture Limits

## Principles

- **KISS:** Simplest solution that satisfies `@docs/PRD.md` offline-first constraints.
- **DRY:** Reuse `@src/lib/*` utilities; do not copy-paste chunking, crypto, or DB logic into components.

## File Size

| Threshold | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| >200 lines | Consider extracting helpers |
| >700 lines | **Must** split before merging |

Split targets:

- Pure logic → `src/lib/` or `src/lib/utils/`
- Sub-UI → colocated folder under `src/components/`
- Phase-specific logic → stay inside `src/components/phases/`

<example>
// WritingPhase.tsx at 750 lines → extract export menu + doc loader to writing/useDocument.ts
</example>

<example type="invalid">
// Append 200 more lines to a 650-line component instead of splitting
</example>

## Layering

```
components/  → UI + hooks only
contexts/    → global providers
lib/         → business logic, no JSX
workers/     → CPU/GPU-heavy tasks
```

- Components must not import from other phase components directly; share via `lib/` or `types.ts`.
- No new backend assumptions — this is a browser-only SPA.

## Dependencies

- Avoid new npm packages unless justified in PRD or ADR.
- Prefer browser APIs (OPFS, WebGPU, IndexedDB) over polyfill servers.
